[2
Date: 7 Jul 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ClicRBS.com [edited
<http://www.clicrbs.com.br/default.jsp?uf=1&local=1&tab=00002&newsID=a65044.htm&subTab=200>

Another 2 animals die with signs of tetanus in the State
---------------------------------------------------------
Another 2 animals died and 3 ill were encountered this Thursday in the
Ranch Paraiso, of Rosario do Sul. On the property, 59 cattle have died and
13 continue with symptoms of the disease. In the Nossa Senhora do Rosario
Ranch, in Sao Gabriel, there are 188 animals dead and 31 ill. On Thursday,
the tetanus [antitoxin vaccine was administered to 155 head of cattle
which had not as yet received a second dose. According to the administrator
Julio Etcheverria, all of the breeding stock of the 2 properties have been
immunized.
--
